personalInfo.bio: Aspiring Junior Frontend Developer with a strong foundation in Visual Communication and Graphic Design. Transitioning into the tech world with a passion for creating pixel-perfect, accessible, and user-friendly web interfaces. Currently focused on mastering React and modern CSS frameworks. A quick learner who thrives in collaborative environments and is eager to apply a keen eye for aesthetics to build seamless digital experiences.

responsibilities: Developing and maintaining responsive landing pages using HTML5, SCSS, and JavaScript (ES6+).
Collaborating with the design team to translate Figma mockups into reusable React components.
Optimizing web assets for performance, ensuring fast loading times across mobile and desktop devices.
Participating in code reviews and daily stand-ups to align with Agile development practices.
Designed and implemented basic website layouts using WordPress and custom CSS.
Created high-fidelity prototypes and wireframes for client projects using Adobe Creative Suite and Figma.
Assisted senior developers in migrating legacy jQuery scripts to modern JavaScript alternatives.
Drafted technical documentation for internal design-to-code handoff processes.

projects.name: Waddle Weather App
projects.description: A sleek, mobile-first weather application tailored for waterfowl, featuring real-time humidity and precipitation alerts using the OpenWeather API.

projects.name: Breadcrumb Hunter UI
